  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil half a kettle and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix until combined</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to the plate and turn them several times until evenly coated in all the spices</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1690284035696-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1690284035696-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1690284035696-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1690284035696-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1690284035696-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken</strong> and any remaining spices and cook for 3 min on each side until browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1690284039595-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1690284039595-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1690284039595-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1690284039595-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1690284039595-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[280ml] </span>[375ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1690284102337-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1690284102337-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1690284102337-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1690284102337-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1690284102337-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your<strong> red kidney beans</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>coriander leaves </strong>from their stalks and set aside for garnish (discard the stalks)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1690284110817-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1690284110817-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1690284110817-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1690284110817-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1690284110817-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>kidney beans</strong>, <strong>tomato stock</strong> and <strong>browned chicken</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25-35 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1690284116413-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1690284116413-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1690284116413-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1690284116413-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1690284116413-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, fold your <strong>tortillas</strong> in half and add them to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1690284077576-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1690284077576-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1690284077576-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1690284077576-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1690284077576-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Return the <strong>shredded chicken</strong> to the dish and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>chicken breast chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-2-1690284129478-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-2-1690284129478-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-2-1690284129478-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-2-1690284129478-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-2-1690284129478-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>chicken breast chilli</strong> with the <strong>warmed tortillas</strong></p><p>Dollop with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> all over and garnish with the <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
